# Why: Per-org "Hide Powered by Pacta" toggle in the existing branding admin
#      UI. Without this, suppressing the email footer attribution required
#      direct DB SQL ‚Äî fine once, painful at scale.
#
#      Documenso already wires `OrganisationClaim.flags.hidePoweredBy`
#      through `getEmailContext` ‚Üí `BrandingSettings.brandingHidePoweredBy`
#      ‚Üí `template-footer.tsx` (where it gates the "Powered by" link).
#      What was missing: a UI to mutate the flag without DB access.
#
#      Implementation strategy: extend the existing
#      `organisation.settings.update` TRPC route + the existing
#      `BrandingPreferencesForm` rather than building a new dedicated
#      route/form. Single mutation atomically updates
#      OrganisationGlobalSettings AND OrganisationClaim.flags. Single form
#      means tenants edit branding + attribution preference together.
#
#      Files modified (all upstream ‚Äî full file diffs in commit):
#        1. packages/trpc/server/organisation-router/update-organisation-settings.types.ts
#           ‚Äî Added `hidePoweredBy?: boolean` to the request schema.
#
#        2. packages/trpc/server/organisation-router/update-organisation-settings.ts
#           ‚Äî When the request includes `hidePoweredBy`, look up the org's
#             OrganisationClaim, merge the flag into the JSON `flags` column,
#             save. Done as a separate prisma call (not nested in the
#             organisation update payload) because Claim is a sibling table
#             with a JSON column ‚Äî easier to handle in isolation.
#
#        3. apps/remix/app/components/forms/branding-preferences-form.tsx
#           ‚Äî Added `hidePoweredBy: z.boolean().optional()` to the zod schema,
#             added `hidePoweredBy` to the props (optional default),
#             threaded into form's defaultValues, rendered a checkbox UI at
#             the bottom of the form (only when context="Organisation"; not
#             shown for teams since the flag is org-level).
#
#        4. apps/remix/app/routes/_authenticated+/o.$orgUrl.settings.branding.tsx
#           ‚Äî Read current flag from `organisationClaim.flags.hidePoweredBy`,
#             pass to the form as `hidePoweredBy` prop, include the form's
#             returned value in the submit payload to TRPC.
#
#      What stays unchanged: the email footer rendering logic
#      (template-footer.tsx, modified by overlay 023) already reads
#      `branding.brandingHidePoweredBy` ‚Äî that field is populated from the
#      claim flag by `organisationGlobalSettingsToBranding()` upstream.
#      No further changes needed there.
#
#      Fragility: MED. Touches 4 upstream files in the per-org settings
#      pipeline. The TRPC route file is the one most likely to see upstream
#      drift (Documenso adds new settings periodically). The form file is
#      stable. Schema file is stable. Page file is stable.
#
#      Trade-off: this approach makes branding-related claim flags special-
#      cased in the org-settings route. If we end up needing to mutate other
#      claim flags from per-org UIs (cfr21, hipaa, etc.) the right move is
#      to factor a separate `organisation.claim.update` TRPC route. For now
#      a focused extension is the minimum viable path.
#
# Files modified (full file diffs in commit):
#   packages/trpc/server/organisation-router/update-organisation-settings.types.ts
#   packages/trpc/server/organisation-router/update-organisation-settings.ts
#   apps/remix/app/components/forms/branding-preferences-form.tsx
#   apps/remix/app/routes/_authenticated+/o.$orgUrl.settings.branding.tsx
